$ Excel: View -> Show

The Menu *View -> Show* can be used to show or some elements on the GUI. The right column shows how these elements
can be manipulated with → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model[Excel's object model]:
table { lll
 ☰ ~Comments~ ☰ ~Object model~
  Ruler ☰ Only applicable in *Page Layout mode* ☰ ?
  Formula Bar ☰ ☰ → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application#excel-application-display-properties[`application.displayFormulaBar`]
  Gridlines ☰ ☰ → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/WorksheetView#excelworksheetView-display-properties[`worksheetView.displayGridlines`]
  Headings ☰ ☰ → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/WorksheetView#excelworksheetView-display-properties[`worksheetView.displayHeadings`]
table }

? Note: *Ruler*, *Gridlines* and *Headings* change the setting for the active → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window[window] only while
*Formula Bar* sets it «globally».
